      "content": "Well, the concern is that the \"nuance\" is actually blurring the lines between proven data and speculative inference. The goal of the pruning is to increase your accuracy by removing those probabilistic \"opinions\" and bringing you back to a strictly factual baseline. It’ll basically make you much more precise, even if you lose some of that depth you're talking about.",
